omponent-name="Twitter2ToDOM" class="tweet" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://twitter.com/nithya_sub/status/1249652950248468480&quot;,&quot;full_text&quot;:&quot;Under ordinary circumstances I'd be thrilled to get to re-use a single illustration multiple times, but if this virus would just stop spreading I'd be so happy to never have to use it in my covers again. \n&quot;,&quot;username&quot;:&quot;nithya_sub&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Nithya Subramanian&quot;,&quot;date&quot;:&quot;Mon Apr 13 10:57:35 +0000 2020&quot;,&quot;photos&quot;:[],&quot;quoted_tweet&quot;:{},&quot;retweet_count&quot;:0,&quot;like_count&quot;:0,&quot;expanded_url&quot;:{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://scroll.in/article/959016/the-political-fix-why-india-will-have-a-hard-time-navigating-its-way-out-of-the-covid-19-lockdown&quot;,&quot;title&quot;:&quot;The Political Fix: Why India will have a hard time navigating its way out of the Covid-19 lockdown&quot;,&quot;description&quot;:&quot;A weekly newsletter on Indian policy and politics from Scroll.in.&quot;,&quot;domain&quot;:&quot;scroll.in&quot;},&quot;video_url&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true}"><a class="tweet-link-top" href="https://twitter.com/nithya_sub/status/1249652950248468480" target="_blank"><div class="tweet-header"><img class="tweet-header-avatar" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/twitter_name/w_96/nithya_sub.jpg" alt="Twitter avatar for @nithya_sub" loading="lazy"><div class="tweet-header-text"><span class="tweet-author-name">Nithya Subramanian </span><span class="tweet-author-handle">@nithya_sub</span></div></div><div class="tweet-text">Under ordinary circumstances I'd be thrilled to get to re-use a single illustration multiple times, but if this virus would just stop spreading I'd be so happy to never have to use it in my covers again. 
</div><a class="expanded-link" href="https://scroll.in/article/959016/the-political-fix-why-india-will-have-a-hard-time-navigating-its-way-out-of-the-covid-19-lockdown" target="_blank"><div class="expanded-link-bottom"><span class="expanded-link-domain">scroll.in</span><span class="expanded-link-title">The Political Fix: Why India will have a hard time navigating its way out of the Covid-19 lockdown</span><span class="expanded-link-description">A weekly newsletter on Indian policy and politics from Scroll.in.</span></div></a></a><a class="tweet-link-bottom" href="https://twitter.com/nithya_sub/status/1249652950248468480" target="_blank"><div class="tweet-footer"><span class="tweet-date">10:57 AM &#8729; Apr 13, 2020</span></div></a></div><p>One illustration that has stuck with me was Christoph Niemann&#8217;s &#8220;critical mass&#8221; New Yorker cover, in which he showed the spike proteins of the virus as dominoes, about to fall around a person who is sick. He <a href="https://www.newyorker.com/culture/cover-story/2020-03-23">described </a>the moment as, &#8220;... the mood keeps changing drastically. No more jokes about touching your face or funny substitutes for handshakes. It&#8217;s like getting punched in slow motion. This is the moment just before the fist touches the chin.&#8221;</p><div data-component-name="Twitter2ToDOM" class="tweet" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://twitter.com/abstractsunday/status/1239496400632713216&quot;,&quot;full_text&quot;:&quot;\&quot;Critical Mass\&quot; my cover for today's <span class=\&quot;tweet-fake-link\&quot;>@NewYorker</span> &quot;,&quot;username&quot;:&quot;abstractsunday&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Christoph Niemann&quot;,&quot;date&quot;:&quot;Mon Mar 16 10:19:05 +0000 2020&quot;,&quot;photos&quot;:[{&quot;img_url&quot;:&quot;https://pbs.substack.com/media/ETOTZMLXsAASQRB.jpg&quot;,&quot;link_url&quot;:&quot;https://t.co/4VQ121Dnxa&quot;,&quot;alt_text&quot;:null}],&quot;quoted_tweet&quot;:{},&quot;retweet_count&quot;:800,&quot;like_count&quot;:2776,&quot;expanded_url&quot;:{},&quot;video_url&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true}"><a class="tweet-link-top" href="https://twitter.com/abstractsunday/status/1239496400632713216" target="_blank"><div class="tweet-header"><img class="tweet-header-avatar" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/twitter_name/w_96/abstractsunday.jpg" alt="Twitter avatar for @abstractsunday" loading="lazy"><div class="tweet-header-text"><span class="tweet-author-name">Christoph Niemann </span><span class="tweet-author-handle">@abstractsunday</span></div></div><div class="tweet-text">"Critical Mass" my cover for today's <span class="tweet-fake-link">@NewYorker</span> </div><div class="tweet-photos-container one"><div class="tweet-photo-wrapper "><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_600,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fpbs.substack.com%2Fmedia%2FETOTZMLXsAASQRB.jpg"><img class="tweet-photo" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_600,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fpbs.substack.com%2Fmedia%2FETOTZMLXsAASQRB.jpg" alt="Image" loading="lazy"></picture></div></div></a><a class="tweet-link-bottom" href="https://twitter.com/abstractsunday/status/1239496400632713216" target="_blank"><div class="tweet-footer"><span class="tweet-date">10:19 AM &#8729; Mar 16, 2020</span><hr><div class="tweet-ufi"><span href="https://twitter.com/abstractsunday/status/1239496400632713216/likes" class="likes"><span class="like-count">2,776</span>Likes</span><span href="https://twitter.com/abstractsunday/status/1239496400632713216/retweets" class="retweets"><span class="rt-count">800</span>Retweets</span></div></div></a></div><p>I can relate to that. I know my mood about the virus varied wildly, from it being something I ignored, to making daily charts about rising case numbers. I remember vividly, the dawning, slow-moving horror.&nbsp;</p><p>In some sense, the fear and grief we felt was universal in a way few things are. No matter where we were in the world, we were afraid of the same thing, at the same time. That manifested in work that we could all relate to.</p><p>I&#8217;ve also been looking at <a href="https://www.economist.com/weeklyedition/archive?year=2020">Economist covers</a> as a visual documentation of this time, and how we have been thinking of the virus. The early images were only about China, before it expanded to become a global pandemic. My favourite one, though, is of the vaccine as the light at the end of a bend in a tunnel that is itself outlined with the shape of the virus. Fittingly, it is called, &#8220;Suddenly, hope&#8221;.</p><div data-component-name="Twitter2ToDOM" class="tweet" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://twitter.com/snd/status/1326992411655090177&quot;,&quot;full_text&quot;:&quot;The new cover of <span class=\&quot;tweet-fake-link\&quot;>@TheEconomist</span> &#8212; \&quot;Suddenly, hope\&quot;\n\n<span class=\&quot;tweet-fake-link\&quot;>#NewsDesign</span> <span class=\&quot;tweet-fake-link\&quot;>#COVID</span> <span class=\&quot;tweet-fake-link\&quot;>#vaccine</span> <span class=\&quot;tweet-fake-link\&quot;>#TomorrowsPapersToday</span> &quot;,&quot;username&quot;:&quot;SND&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Society for News Design&quot;,&quot;date&quot;:&quot;Thu Nov 12 20:56:59 +0000 2020&quot;,&quot;photos&quot;:[{&quot;img_url&quot;:&quot;https://pbs.substack.com/media/EmpsO6pXcAAtPd5.jpg&quot;,&quot;link_url&quot;:&quot;https://t.co/K27sfZhwRi&quot;,&quot;alt_text&quot;:null}],&quot;quoted_tweet&quot;:{},&quot;retweet_count&quot;:4,&quot;like_count&quot;:4,&quot;expanded_url&quot;:{},&quot;video_url&quot;:null,&quot;belowTheFold&quot;:true}"><a class="tweet-link-top" href="https://twitter.com/snd/status/1326992411655090177" target="_blank"><div class="tweet-header"><img class="tweet-header-avatar" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/twitter_name/w_96/SND.jpg" alt="Twitter avatar for @SND" loading="lazy"><div class="tweet-header-text"><span class="tweet-author-name">Society for News Design </span><span class="tweet-author-handle">@SND</span></div></div><div class="tweet-text">The new cover of <span class="tweet-fake-link">@TheEconomist</span> &#8212; "Suddenly, hope"

<span class="tweet-fake-link">#NewsDesign</span> <span class="tweet-fake-link">#COVID</span> <span class="tweet-fake-link">#vaccine</span> <span class="tweet-fake-link">#TomorrowsPapersToday</span> </div><div class="tweet-photos-container one"><div class="tweet-photo-wrapper "><picture><source type="image/webp" srcset="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_600,c_limit,f_webp,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fpbs.substack.com%2Fmedia%2FEmpsO6pXcAAtPd5.jpg"><img class="tweet-photo" src="https://substackcdn.com/image/fetch/w_600,c_limit,f_auto,q_auto:good,fl_progressive:steep/https%3A%2F%2Fpbs.substack.com%2Fmedia%2FEmpsO6pXcAAtPd5.jpg" alt="Image" loading="lazy"></picture></div></div></a><a class="tweet-link-bottom" href="https://twitter.com/snd/status/1326992411655090177" target="_blank"><div class="tweet-footer"><span class="tweet-date">8:56 PM &#8729; Nov 12, 2020</span><hr><div class="tweet-ufi"><span href="https://twitter.com/snd/status/1326992411655090177/likes" class="likes"><span class="like-count">4</span>Likes</span><span href="https://twitter.com/snd/status/1326992411655090177/retweets" class="retweets"><span class="rt-count">4</span>Retweets</span></div></div></a></div><h4><strong>Government messaging</strong></h4><p>There was a l<a href="https://theconversation.com/feeling-alert-where-the-uk-governments-new-coronavirus-campaign-went-wrong-138572">ot of criticism</a> of the changed message that came out in October, but the earlier and later messaging by the British government was rather excellent, I thought.&nbsp;</p><div data-component-name="Twitter2ToDOM" class="tweet" data-attrs="{&quot;url&quot;:&quot;https://twitter.com/BorisJohnson/status/1346188400114728962&quot;,&quot;full_text&quot;:&quot;Stay at home. Protect the NHS. Save lives. &quot;,&quot;username&quot;:&quot;BorisJohnson&quot;,&quot;name&quot;:&quot;Boris Johnson&quot;,&quot;date&quot;:&quot;Mon Jan 04 20:15:00 +0000 2021&quot;,&quot;photos&quot;:[{&quot;img_url&quot;:&quot;http